## Development Workflow

### Commands
```bash
pnpm install          # Install dependencies
pnpm dev             # Development server (port 3000)
pnpm build           # Production build
pnpm start           # Production server
pnpm lint            # ESLint checking
```

### Environment Variables
```env
DATABASE_URL=        # Neon PostgreSQL connection string
EMAIL_HOST=          # SMTP server for notifications
EMAIL_PORT=          # SMTP port (587)
EMAIL_USER=          # SMTP username
EMAIL_PASS=          # SMTP password
EMAIL_FROM=         # From email address
WEBHOOK_URL=         # Optional webhook for notifications
```

### Content Creation
Blog posts are created as `.md` files in `content/blog/` with frontmatter:
```yaml
---
title: "Post Title"
description: "Post description"
date: "2024-01-01"
author: "Author Name"
tags: ["tag1", "tag2"]
featured: true
published: true
image: "optional-image-url"
thumbnail: "thumbnail-filename.jpg"
cover: "cover-filename.jpg"
---
```

## Deployment

### Vercel Configuration
- Automatic deployments via GitHub Actions
- Static blog generation at build time
- Security headers for blog routes
- CSP headers configured

### Build Optimization
- ESLint and TypeScript checks disabled in build
- Content tracing for blog files
- Image optimization enabled

## Code Style & Conventions

### Naming Conventions
- **Components**: PascalCase (e.g., `HeroSection`, `BlogCard`)
- **Files**: kebab-case (e.g., `nav-bar.tsx`, `blog-section.tsx`)
- **Functions**: camelCase (e.g., `getPostBySlug`, `subscribeToNewsletter`)

### Component Patterns
- Client components marked with `"use client"`
- Server actions in `app/actions.ts`
- Custom hooks in `lib/` directory
- SVG components as React components

### Error Handling
- Graceful degradation for missing data
- Comprehensive error logging
- User-friendly error messages in Spanish

### Security
- DOMPurify for HTML sanitization
- Zod schemas for validation
- CSP headers configured
- XSS prevention in blog content

## Internationalization
- Primary language: Spanish (Argentina)
- All user-facing text in Spanish
- HTML lang attribute set to "es"

## Performance Considerations
- Static blog data generation
- Image optimization with Next.js
- Framer Motion for smooth animations
- Lazy loading for components
- Minimal bundle size with tree shaking

## Testing & Debugging
- Health check endpoints (`/api/health`)
- Debug routes for database (`/api/debug-db`)
- Email testing routes (`/api/debug-email`)
- Comprehensive error logging

## Maintenance Notes
- Blog posts require rebuild for static generation
- Database schema changes need migration scripts
- Email templates may need updates for branding changes
- SVG logos are customizable React components

This project represents a modern, well-architected Next.js application with excellent separation of concerns, security practices, and user experience considerations.